```
useEffect(() => {
  let ws = new WebSocket(url);
  let reconnectTimer;

  ws.onmessage = (e) => {
    const data = JSON.parse(e.data);
    setMessages(prev => [...prev, data]);
  };
  ws.onclose = () => {
    reconnectTimer = setTimeout(() => {
      ws = new WebSocket(url); // reconnect
    }, 3000);
  };

  return () => {
    clearTimeout(reconnectTimer);
    ws.close();
  };
}, [url]);
```

Pitfall 1: the message handler uses a functional updater (prev => [...prev, data]) to avoid stale closure on messages. Pitfall 2: cleanup must close the socket AND clear the reconnect timer, or you get zombie connections. Pitfall 3: the `url` dependency means changing rooms triggers cleanup → reconnect.

